The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has scheduled its  North-West zonal congress for February 12, 2022. The PDP in a statement by its National Organizing Secretary, Hon. Umaru M. Bature said the decision was reached at a meeting of the  National Working Committee (NWC) on Wednesday. “The North-West Zonal Congress is slated to hold at the Zonal Headquarters of the party in Kaduna State. “All critical stakeholders and teeming members of our great party in the North-West Zone are by this informed and guided accordingly,” the party siad. Meanwhile, the National Working Committee (NWC) of the PDP has inaugurated three committees to restore sanity in the party and “rescue” Nigeria. They are; Tenders Committee; Committee for the Review of Party’s Establishment Manual and Scheme of Service, and Staff Audit Committee. Inaugurating the committees yesterday in Abuja, the National Secretary of the party, Senator Samuel Anyanwu, said for the party to rescue and rebuild Nigeria, it must bring real change to party administration.